# Netflix Data Analysis

## Dataset
Netflix Titles Dataset

This dataset contains information about movies and TV shows available on Netflix, including type, country, release year, rating, and genre.

Dataset Source:
Kaggle

## Tools Used
Google Sheets  
Pivot Tables  
Data Cleaning  
Data Visualization  

## Objective
Analyze Netflix content to understand the distribution of movies and TV shows, identify top content-producing countries, and observe how the platform's catalog has grown over time.

## Data Cleaning
Some fields contained missing values, particularly in columns such as director and country. The dataset was analyzed and organized to allow aggregation and visualization using pivot tables.

## Analysis

### 1. Movies vs TV Shows Distribution
A pivot table was used to count the number of Movies and TV Shows available on Netflix.

### 2. Top Content Producing Countries
Content was grouped by country to identify which countries contribute the most titles to the Netflix catalog.

### 3. Content Growth Over Time
Content was grouped by release year to visualize how the number of titles has increased over time.

## Key Insights

• Movies represent the majority of Netflix content compared to TV Shows.

• The United States produces the largest amount of content available on Netflix.

• The number of titles added to the catalog increased significantly after 2015, reflecting Netflix’s rapid global expansion.

